ppearing regularly. This volume sheds light on the most relevant pieces of evidence for ancient Orphism, collected in the recent edition by Alberto Bernabé. It contains 65 short new studies on Orphic fragments by leading international scholars who comment one of the most controversial phenomena in Antiquity from a plurality of perspectives. Readers will acquire a global vision of the multiple dimensions of the Orphic tradition, as well as many new insights into particular Orphic fragments.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aDionysos. 4aGriechische Literatur. 4aGriechische Philosophie. 4aGriechische Religion. 4aOrphismus. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aDionysos.  aGreek Literature.  aGreek Philosophy.  aGreek Religion.  aOrphism.1 aAguilar, Rosa M.ª, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAguirre, Mercedes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerenguer-Sánchez, José A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBetegh, Gábor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBierl, Anton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoned, Pilar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBremmer, Jan N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrisson, Luc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurkert, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCabrera, Paloma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaerols, José Joaquín, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalame, Claude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalvo Martín